title: [Vornavian Coast, Beach]
description: Waves crash over a stubborn rock outcropping that has defied the erosion of the shore over the years.  Moonlight reflects off the crest of each wave and sounds of the surf breaking on the beach are carried on the night air.

Waves crash over a stubborn rock outcropping that has defied the erosion of the shore over the years.  Seagulls perch on the outcropping, cracking shellfish with their beaks.  Hermit crabs scurry in and out of cracks in the moss-covered rocks, burying themselves in the soft sands.
